      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The Python stdlib module "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ":external+python:mod:`random`"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " contains\npseudo-random number generator with a number of methods that are similar\nto the ones available in "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Generator"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ".\nIt uses Mersenne Twister, and this bit generator can\nbe accessed using "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "MT19937"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Generator"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", besides being\nNumPy-aware, has the advantage that it provides a much larger number\nof probability distributions to choose from."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
